getError

public double getError(Instance instance,
                       Hashtable<NeuralNode,Double> nodeValues)
Returns the error of the current element. If the value have not been calculated an IllegalStateException will be thrown. If the error have not been calculated it will be first calculated.

Parameters:
instance - the current instance that is passed through the network
nodeValues - the collection of values calculated so far
Returns:
the error of the element
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if value have not been calculated yet

updateWeights

public void updateWeights(Instance instance,
                          Hashtable<NeuralNode,Double> nodeValues,
                          double learn,
                          double momentum)
Call this function to update the weight values at this element. After the weights have been updated at this element, All the input connections will then be called from this to have their weights updated.

Parameters:
instance - the current instance that is passed through the network
nodeValues - the node values calculated so far
learn - The learning Rate to use.
momentum - The momentum to use.

reset

public void reset(Hashtable<NeuralNode,Double> nodeValues)
This function will reset the current element and all its input elements in initial state as if no calculations were performed. The current element will be ready for the next teaching example.

Parameters:
nodeValues - the values for all neural nodes for the current running instance of the algorithm, which have been calculated so far

changeWeight

public double changeWeight(int inputElementIndex,
                           double newValue)
Changes the weight of the corresponding input connection on the specified input element index. Implementations should update the corresponding weight change in order to be able to achieve certain optimizations.

Parameters:
inputElementIndex - the index of the input element connection to be updated
newValue - the new weight of the connection
